# Priority 5 — Investigate Networking Terraform Change

This becomes highly suspicious because:

### Timeline Correlation

```text
Terraform change morning
Incident starts later
No app deploy
```

Networking is now highest-probability domain.

---

## Pull Terraform Change

Review:

```text
PR
Change record
Terraform plan
```

Questions:

Did they modify:

### Firewall Rules

```text
deny
allow
target tags
service accounts
```

---

### Network Tags

Very common issue.

Example:

```text
old-tag
gke-prod-node
```

changed to:

```text
zscaler-prod-node
```

One nodepool updated.

Others not.

Now subset of nodes lose connectivity.

---

### Routes

Check:

```text
custom routes
default route
PSC routes
```

---

### Cloud NAT

If inference service reaches:

```text
Model API
Artifact Registry
External service
```

and Cloud NAT broke for subset of nodes:

some requests fail.

---

# Priority 6 — Verify Firewall Logs and Connectivity

Use:

```text
VPC Flow Logs
Firewall Insights
Connectivity Tests
```

---

## Connectivity Test

```bash
gcloud network-management connectivity-tests create
```

Validate:

```text
GKE Pod
 →
Dependency
```

---

## VPC Flow Logs

Questions:

Do we see:

```text
DENY
REJECT
TIMEOUT
```

for specific node IPs?

This often identifies networking misconfigurations quickly.

---

# Priority 7 — Cloud SQL Validation

Cloud SQL CPU is normal.

But I still verify:

---

## Connection Metrics

Monitoring:

```text
database/postgresql/num_backends
```

Check:

```text
connection count
connection saturation
```

---

### Why?

One pod may be leaking connections.

Result:

```text
5 pods succeed
1 pod fails
```

Still matches 1-in-6 pattern.

---

## Cloud SQL Logs

Look for:

```text
too many connections
authentication failures
```

---

# Priority 8 — Error Reporting

Open:

```text
Error Reporting
```

Check:

```text
new error signature
```

started

```text
30 minutes ago
```

Questions:

* Same stack trace?
* Same pod?
* Same dependency?

This often narrows investigation dramatically.

